          "warnings": [],
          "notes": []
        },
        {
          "step": 5,
          "text": "Calculate connecting rod bearing clearance. Connecting rod bearing clearance = Inner dia. \u2013 Outer dia.",
          "figure_ref": null,
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": []
        },
        {
          "step": 6,
          "text": "If it exceeds the limit, replace bearing.",
          "figure_ref": null,
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": []
        },
        {
          "step": 7,
          "text": "If clearance cannot be adjusted within the standard of any bearing, grind crankshaft journal and use undersized bearing. Refer to step 7 of \"BEARING CLEARANCE \u2014 Main bearing\".",
